    "what_description": "Origanum vulgare is a perennial herbaceous plant belonging to the family Lamiaceae. It has a woody base, with several stems emerging from the base, and a height of 20-80 cm, with a spread of 30-50 cm. The leaves are lanceolate, 2-4 cm long, and 5-10 mm wide, with a crenate margin and a hairy surface. The flowers are purple, tubular, and 4-6 mm long, in a terminal spike, and are borne in the summer months. The plant is native to Europe, Western Asia, and North Africa, and is naturalized in many other parts of the world.",
